1294
01:27:58,024 --> 01:28:00,444
<i>Don't throw our love away.</i>

1295
01:28:00,902 --> 01:28:04,406
<i>In my arms you'll always stay.</i>

1296
01:28:04,489 --> 01:28:07,409
<i>Baby love, my baby love.</i>

1297
01:28:07,659 --> 01:28:11,872
<i>I need ya, oh, how I need ya.</i>

1298
01:28:16,877 --> 01:28:20,297
Come on now. Let's hurry up.
Get those cars started.

1299
01:28:20,714 --> 01:28:22,215
<i>ANNOUNCER: Looks like some
of the local drivers</i>

1300
01:28:22,299 --> 01:28:24,050
<i>are intentionally slowing down the pace,</i>

1301
01:28:24,134 --> 01:28:26,386
<i>trying to buy Milner some extra time.</i>

1302
01:28:27,095 --> 01:28:31,141
<i>From here I can see the competitors,
who are usually feuding with each other,</i>

1303
01:28:31,224 --> 01:28:34,394
<i>all helping out in Milner's cause.
Incredible!</i>

1304
01:28:35,270 --> 01:28:36,480
(CROWD CHEERING)

1305
01:28:36,563 --> 01:28:39,441
<i>Here's the Hunt Brothers' car,
prepared for the kill.</i>

1306
01:28:39,524 --> 01:28:43,195
<i>They fully expect to win.
The factory demands they win.</i>

1307
01:28:54,831 --> 01:28:57,000
<i>Minutes to go, still no Milner.</i>

1308
01:28:57,083 --> 01:29:01,880
<i>Looks like the Hunt Brothers are about to
demand a single-run victory by default.</i>

1309
01:29:03,298 --> 01:29:06,218
- Carlos, you got those plugs changed?
- Yeah.

1310
01:29:06,468 --> 01:29:08,803
I got you some fuel here, John.

1311
01:29:09,262 --> 01:29:12,807
- I got my own mixture. 90%.
- You'll blow your engine, man.

1312
01:29:13,600 --> 01:29:15,852
<i>ANNOUNCER: Still no sign of John Milner.</i>

1313
01:29:15,936 --> 01:29:20,315
<i>He knows the rules. If you're not on
the line in time, you're disqualified.</i>

1314
01:29:26,363 --> 01:29:28,907
- Okay, we got it.
- We'll never make it.

1315
01:29:28,990 --> 01:29:30,408
Come on, man! Let's go!

1316
01:29:31,201 --> 01:29:34,371
<i>ANNOUNCER: Frankly, it doesn't look good.
There's so little time left.</i>

1317
01:29:34,454 --> 01:29:38,542
<i>Probably a single run for the Hunt
Brothers, Milner losing by default.</i>

1318
01:29:38,625 --> 01:29:41,253
<i>But hold it! Look, over
on the fire-up road.</i>

1319
01:29:41,503 --> 01:29:44,881
<i>Against all odds Milner has got it moving!</i>

1320
01:30:02,649 --> 01:30:03,900
<i>Milner's made it to the line</i>

1321
01:30:03,984 --> 01:30:07,195
<i>but that's just half
of this incredible mechanical miracle.</i>

1322
01:30:07,279 --> 01:30:10,574
<i>After all their patchwork,
will the car go straight down the track?</i>

1323
01:30:10,657 --> 01:30:13,827
<i>Will it go straight into the guard rail?
It's a big gamble.</i>

1324
01:30:18,290 --> 01:30:19,624
Do you think that front
end's gonna hold up?

